results of component 1 (month 7);   
2.4   Develop a draft dissemination plan for the development and use of the platform 
(month 7); 
2.5  Submit final survey report (month 8); 
2.6  Submit an interim report on component 2 (month 9). 

Component 3: Establishment of the energy conservation platform 
3.1  Engage information technology and database development services (month 5); 
3.2  Develop database on energy-saving information, technologies, experts, available 
resources, opportunities, etc. (month 9); 
3.3  Develop  website  for  the  ECP;  identify  and  integrate  links  with  international 
networks for proven energy conservation technologies and practices (month 10); 
3.4  Integrate  the  energy  conservation  technology  service  teams  created  by  the 
executing agency to provide energy conservation technology service to the six 
selected industries (month 10); 
3.5  Integrate the energy conservation alliance and network that will be developed by 
the executing and implementing agencies among the technology service agents 
within the Bohai Rim region (month 11); 
3.6  Submit a written report and documentation of the ECP (month 12). 

Component 4: Selection of priority pilot projects  
4.1  Determine possible energy conservation and efficiency projects that can be 
supported in the order of priority through the ECP; provide the rationale for 
selecting suggested projects, including impact and benefit analysis, technical 
considerations, investment needs and financing options, and implementation 
schedules (month 11); 
4.2  Identify critical issues to be addressed and steps to be taken by TMG, including 
possible  barriers  and  assistance  required  to  develop  the  proposed  projects 
(month 11); 
4.3  Analyze  the  financing  needs  and  develop  an  investment  plan  for  energy 
conservation in the selected industries (month 11); 
4.4  Submit a draft final report (month 13). 

Component 5: Capacity development and information dissemination 
5.1  Conduct a consultation workshop (month 8);  
5.2  Conduct an international field study program for selected staff of the executing 
and implementing agencies, and submit a field study report (month 10);  
5.3  Develop a public dissemination strategy to promote the use of the ECP by 
various  industries,  and  share  the  TA  outputs  with  other  municipalities  and 
provinces within the Bohai Rim region; develop guidelines and materials for 
dissemination (month 11); 
5.4  Train the executing and implementing agencies on the operation, maintenance 
and upgrade of the ECP (month 13); 
5.5  Conduct the final workshop; disclose the TA results on the websites of local 
governments; summarize main TA findings and share with a broad audience; 
and, if possible, prepare a news release for local media in Tianjin (month 14); 
5.6  Submit the final report (month 15). 
ADB = Asian Development Bank, ECP = Energy conservation platform, PRC = People's Republic of China, TA = technical 
assistance, TMG = Tianjin municipal government, TSTC = Tianjin Science and Technology Commission.
